distal segment of maxilla. Scale bars: 0.2 mm (
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">A</emphasis>
); 0.05 mm (
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">B, C</emphasis>
); 0.02 mm (
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">D-I</emphasis>
).
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
Rostrum represented by spatulate anterior prominence of cephalothorax (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 7" captionStartId="F7" captionText="Figure 7. Pontoclausia cochleata sp. nov., female A habitus, dorsal B caudal rami, dorsal C antennule D antenna E labrum F mandible G maxillule H maxilla I distal segment of maxilla. Scale bars: 0.2 mm (A); 0.05 mm (B, C); 0.02 mm (D-I)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1115.83266.figure7" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/720727" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">7A</figureCitation>
). Antennule (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 7" captionStartId="F7" captionText="Figure 7. Pontoclausia cochleata sp. nov., female A habitus, dorsal B caudal rami, dorsal C antennule D antenna E labrum F mandible G maxillule H maxilla I distal segment of maxilla. Scale bars: 0.2 mm (A); 0.05 mm (B, C); 0.02 mm (D-I)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1115.83266.figure7" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/720727" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">7C</figureCitation>
) short, 190 
<normalizedToken originalValue="μm">μm</normalizedToken>
long, five-segmented; armature formula 3, 24, 4+aesthetasc, 2+aesthetasc, and 7+aesthetasc; all setae naked; aesthetascs tapering in distal part; first segment with few minute spinules on proximal anterior margin. Antenna (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 7" captionStartId="F7" captionText="Figure 7. Pontoclausia cochleata sp. nov., female A habitus, dorsal B caudal rami, dorsal C antennule D antenna E labrum F mandible G maxillule H maxilla I distal segment of maxilla. Scale bars: 0.2 mm (A); 0.05 mm (B, C); 0.02 mm (D-I)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1115.83266.figure7" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/720727" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">7D</figureCitation>
) three-segmented; first segment (coxobasis) longest, with one seta at inner distal corner and hair-like setules on outer margin; second segment (first endopodal segment) with one seta subdistally and two groups of spinules on inner surface; third segment (fused second and third endopodal segments) armed with one claw plus two setae on inner margin, four claws distally (outermost claw longest, bearing two minute spinules subdistally on inner margin), three setae on subdistal outer margin (middle one naked, but other two pinnate), and ornamented with three patches of spinules (two patches on outer side and one on proximal inner margin).
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
Labrum (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 7" captionStartId="F7" captionText="Figure 7. Pontoclausia cochleata sp. nov., female A habitus, dorsal B caudal rami, dorsal C antennule D antenna E labrum F mandible G maxillule H maxilla I distal segment of maxilla. Scale bars: 0.2 mm (A); 0.05 mm (B, C); 0.02 mm (D-I)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1115.83266.figure7" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/720727" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">7E</figureCitation>
) small, not covering mouthparts, with protuberance in middle of posterior margin and large, tapering, beak-like process on dorsal surface. Mandible (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 7" captionStartId="F7" captionText="Figure 7. Pontoclausia cochleata sp. nov., female A habitus, dorsal B caudal rami, dorsal C antennule D antenna E labrum F mandible G maxillule H maxilla I distal segment of maxilla. Scale bars: 0.2 mm (A); 0.05 mm (B, C); 0.02 mm (D-I)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1115.83266.figure7" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/720727" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">7F</figureCitation>
) unarmed but highly transformed; its distal part curved, tapering, scoop-like. Maxillule (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 7" captionStartId="F7" captionText="Figure 7. Pontoclausia cochleata sp. nov., female A habitus, dorsal B caudal rami, dorsal C antennule D antenna E labrum F mandible G maxillule H maxilla I distal segment of maxilla. Scale bars: 0.2 mm (A); 0.05 mm (B, C); 0.02 mm (D-I)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1115.83266.figure7" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/720727" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">7G</figureCitation>
) as foot-like lobe, distally expanded medially, armed with four setae (two outer ones longer than other two); broadened distal surface covered with numerous spinules. Maxilla (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 7" captionStartId="F7" captionText="Figure 7. Pontoclausia cochleata sp. nov., female A habitus, dorsal B caudal rami, dorsal C antennule D antenna E labrum F mandible G maxillule H maxilla I distal segment of maxilla. Scale bars: 0.2 mm (A); 0.05 mm (B, C); 0.02 mm (D-I)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1115.83266.figure7" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/720727" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">7H</figureCitation>
) two-segmented; proximal segment (syncoxa) unarmed, ~ twice longer than wide; distal segment (basis; Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 7" captionStartId="F7" captionText="Figure 7. Pontoclausia cochleata sp. nov., female A habitus, dorsal B caudal rami, dorsal C antennule D antenna E labrum F mandible G maxillule H maxilla I distal segment of maxilla. Scale bars: 0.2 mm (A); 0.05 mm (B, C); 0.02 mm (D-I)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1115.83266.figure7" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/720727" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">7I</figureCitation>
) blunt, with two spinulose pads apically, armed with two small subdistal setae each on inner and outer margins. Maxilliped (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 8" captionStartId="F8" captionText="Figure 8. Pontoclausia cochleata sp. nov., female A maxilliped B leg 1 C leg 2 D leg 3 E leg 4 F leg 5. Scale bars: 0.02 mm (A); 0.05 mm (B-E); 0.1 mm (F)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1115.83266.figure8" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/720728" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">8A</figureCitation>
) as unsegmented, tapering lobe tipped with one naked seta, ornamented with two subapical rows of setules (or spinules).
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
Legs 1-4 (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 8" captionStartId="F8" captionText="Figure 8. Pontoclausia cochleata sp. nov., female A maxilliped B leg 1 C leg 2 D leg 3 E leg 4 F leg 5. Scale bars: 0.02 mm (A); 0.05 mm (B-E); 0.1 mm (F)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1115.83266.figure8" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/720728" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">8B-E</figureCitation>
) biramous, with three-segmented rami; both rami of each leg slender, almost equal in length. Coxa lacking inner seta but ornamented with spinules on outer distal corner. Basis with spinules on distal margin between rami; outer seta long, naked. Terminal spine on third exopodal segment of legs 1-4 characteristically unequally bifurcate at tip. Armature formula for legs 1-4 as follows:
</paragraph>
