<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
Rostrum as in female. Antennule and antenna segmented and armed as in female. Labrum, mandible, maxillule, and maxilla also as in female. Maxilliped (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 9" captionStartId="F9" captionText="Figure 9. Pontoclausia cochleata sp. nov., male A habitus, dorsal B urosome, dorsal C left caudal ramus, dorsal D maxilliped E leg 1 F distal part of endopod of leg 1. Scale bars: 0.1 mm (A); 0.05 mm (B, C); 0.02 mm (D, F); 0.05 mm (E)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1115.83266.figure9" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/720729" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">9D</figureCitation>
